
@author Valentine Chiwome

This project implements a distributed hash table using
"chord". It creates several processes on the same machine
and these processes communicate using UDP. I have used
UDP because the probability of packet loss/packet reordering
on a single machine is extremely low.

To run this project, go to the package "test" and run
"PeerA", "PeerB", "PeerC" and "Client" in that order.
You will see that the key, value pairs that are added
by "Client" are stored at the right nodes in the network.
You can see this by examining the consoles of different 
processes.